The door was locked. The only way she’d escape was by shattering the windows and jumping outside, so leaving the apartment was impossible. No one would save her in this city.
EunHa stretched out lifelessly on the dusty sofa like a marionette as she began to think.
She decided that the moment that door opened, she’d kill who she used to be and live on.
Like this, the crybaby, scaredy-cat sixteen-year-old girl was slowly being killed off.



